HEADWORD: Decorative
<hw>Dec"o*ra*tive</hw> <pr>(d⟦ecr⟧k"⟦osl⟧*r⟦adot⟧*t⟦icr⟧v <it>or</it>
d⟦ecr⟧k"⟦osl⟧*r⟦asl⟧*t⟦icr⟧v)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>d⟦eacute⟧coratif</ets>.]</ety> <def>Suited to decorate or
embellish; adorning.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Dec"o*ra*tive*ness</wf>,
<pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Decorative art</b></col>, <cd>fine art which has for its
end ornamentation, rather than the representation of objects or
events.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Decorator</ent>⟦br⟧
